# Builder GPS uses per-app env files. There is no longer a shared root .env.
# Each app reads only its own env vars — see the example in each folder:
#
#   apps/api/.env.example   → backend (Groq key, CORS, model ids, SQLite path)
#   apps/web/.env.example   → frontend (NEXT_PUBLIC_* — API URL + CTA URLs)
#
# To get started locally:
#
#   cp apps/api/.env.example apps/api/.env       # then paste GROQ_API_KEY
#   cp apps/web/.env.example apps/web/.env.local # optional, all vars optional
#
# Production: set the same vars in your hosting platform's env dashboard
# (Fly.io / Railway for the API, Vercel for the web app).
